title.narrative: HEALTH RESPONSE TO COVID-19

description.narrative: Contribute to the response plan for the prevention and control of COVID-19, in territories of greater transmissibility, so that children and their families can receive health care of higher quality and hygienic conditions to contain the disease spreading., which contributes to Climate Change, Disaster Risks And Envionmental Degradation, Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids (Covid), Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care (Covid), Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Safe And Equitable Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Services And Practices, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid), Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Systems And Empowerment Of Communities. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2024, children, adolescents and their families in prioritized territories receive better quality health care for their well- being and development, even in emergencies.

description.narrative: In the year 2021, marked by a complex epidemiological situation due to the pandemic caused by COVID-19, UNICEF-CO, sustained by the Basic Commitments for Childhood in Humanitarian Action, in alliance with MINSAP, Civil Defense, local governments and other organizations, supported the response to the health emergency in territories with greater vulnerability throughout the country, directly benefitting more than 642 healthcare centers including those in the community level, more than 191,064 vulnerable people, including healthcare professionals, and reaching more than 4,900,000 people in digital platforms with communication and awareness actions. | Status:Met | As-of Date:13/01/2022
